        <question id="acces-q10" type="A" hidden="false">
            <text>Do your users login to your systems with personal accounts?</text>
            <attachments/>
            <options correct="acces-q10o1">
                <option id="acces-q10o1">
                    <text>YES, FOR ALL SYSTEMS WE USE</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q10o2">
                    <text>YES, FOR MOST SYSTEMS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q10o3">
                    <text>YES, FOR SOME SYSTEMS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q10o4">
                    <text>NO, OUR SYSTEMS ARE OPEN OR THE ACCOUNTS ARE SHARED</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
            </options>
            <listeners/>
            <metadata key="scores">
                <mvalue key="acces-q10o1">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
                <mvalue key="acces-q10o2">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <metadata key="nextQid">
                <mvalue key="default">
                    <stringValue>acces-q20</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stop password sharing! &lt;/strong&gt;Even if your colleague asks for it. And never ask a person for their passwords/accounts. Passwords should not be shared with anyone to avoid internal security issues&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.isdecisions.com/blog/it-security/protection-from-password-sharing/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Don't negate the benefit of authentication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;! &lt;/strong&gt;You need the ability to audit and monitor a specific user&amp;rsquo;s actions. Statistics show that SMEs have problems regarding employees&amp;rsquo; password practices such as password sharing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/458857/Password_guidance_-_simplifying_your_approach.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply these approaches instead of sharing passwords/accounts: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Use delegation of permission options&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Use alternate access control mechanisms such as applying a hardware token&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;create a new account with an appropriate level of access&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cmu.edu/iso/governance/guidelines/password-management.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/Rq3Ph_vRiEM&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
        <question id="acces-q20" type="text" hidden="false">
        <text>Please list the systems that are open or offer shared accounts.</text>
        <attachments/>
        <listeners/>
        <metadata key="scores">
            <mvalue key="acces-q20o1">
                <stringValue>50</stringValue>
            </mvalue>
            <mvalue key="acces-q20o2">
                <stringValue>50</stringValue>
            </mvalue>
        </metadata>
        <metadata key="nextQid">
            <mvalue key="default">
                <stringValue>acces-q30</stringValue>
            </mvalue>
        </metadata>
        <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are you!&lt;/strong&gt; The owner of the account is responsible for any action performed with the account, even if another person was using that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://news.sunybroome.edu/focus/top-reasons-why-you-shouldnt-share-your-username-and-password/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why avoid using a shared account!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;To protect your private information&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;To make others secure by preventing unauthorised access to the systems.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;To increase the accountability for the account&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;To decrease the password management risks (sharing password, former employees, &amp;hellip;)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sans.org/reading-room/whitepapers/basics/administration-shared-accounts-1271&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/pJpmCXtLZ8I&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
        <question id="acces-q30" type="A" hidden="false">
            <text>Do your users use a different password for each of their accounts?</text>
            <attachments/>
            <options correct="acces-q30o1">
                <option id="acces-q30o1">
                    <text>YES, ALL OUR USERS USE DIFFERENT PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q30o2">
                    <text>NO, SOME USERS REUSE SOME PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q30o3">
                    <text>NO, WE DO NOT CONTROL PASSWORD USE</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q30o4">
                    <text>WE USE AUTHORIZATION MECHANISMS OTHER THAN PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
            </options>
            <listeners/>
            <metadata key="scores">
                <mvalue key="acces-q30o1">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
                <mvalue key="acces-q30o2">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <metadata key="nextQid">
                <mvalue key="default">
                    <stringValue>acces-q40</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End dangerous practices! &lt;/strong&gt;Studies indicate that reusing the same password for different services is a common dangerous strategy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pandasecurity.com/mediacenter/security/password-reuse/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why not password reuse! &lt;/strong&gt;If a reused password is stolen it can be applied for unauthorized access to multiple systems.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.researchgate.net/publication/251232396_Improving_Password_Cybersecurity_Through_Inexpensive_and_Minimally_Invasive_Means_Detecting_and_Deterring_Password_Reuse_Through_Keystroke-Dynamics_Monitoring_and_Just-in-Time_Fear_Appeals&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How can I deal with password reuse problem!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable enhanced security. &lt;/strong&gt;Then you can receive a request for additional information if you login into a site from a new location or computer.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify and change.&lt;/strong&gt; Where else you may have applied this password.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delete those accounts you no longer require.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply single sign-on (SSO) technology&lt;/strong&gt;. The ability to authenticate once and never have to repeat the process for the duration of the session and password synchronization. It can mitigate the problem by removing the need to create new login credentials. You can only memorize a password and access to multiple accounts.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply biometrics as a viable solution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;Biometric systems such as a fingerprint can be applied to manage password fatigue. It is easy to use and it can be combined with a PIN.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://securityintelligence.com/a-proposed-solution-to-the-password-reuse-problem/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;iframe src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/zPpFjX71-w8&quot; width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;allowfullscreen&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
        <question id="acces-q40" type="A" hidden="false">
            <text>Do your users use any other authentication method such as fingerprint or 2-factor to access your sensitive systems?</text>
            <attachments/>
            <options correct="acces-q40o1">
                <option id="acces-q40o1">
                    <text>YES, FOR ALL SYSTEMS WE USE</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q40o2">
                    <text>YES, FOR MOST SYSTEMS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q40o3">
                    <text>YES, FOR SOME SYSTEMS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q40o4">
                    <text>NO, WE ONLY USE PASSWORD AUTHENTICATION</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
            </options>
            <listeners/>
            <metadata key="scores">
                <mvalue key="acces-q40o1">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
                <mvalue key="acces-q40o2">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <metadata key="nextQid">
                <mvalue key="default">
                    <stringValue>acces-q50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Makes it harder to get into your account! &lt;/strong&gt;Passwords are one way of authentication while there are other forms of verifying users&amp;rsquo; identity such as fingerprints, 2/multiple-factor authentication (2FA), applying hardware or software tokens, or smart cards which you can add extra security layer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://auth0.com/blog/why-every-business-needs-two-factor-authentication-security/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why 2FA! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Even strong passwords cannot protect you against data breaches or key logger attacks. Key logging programs can track all your keystrokes including your account credentials.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://authanvil.com/blog/3-types-of-password-security-attacks-and-how-to-avoid-them&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activate dual-factor authentication for your significant accounts such as emails.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to enable 2FA! &lt;/strong&gt;Some websites and services offer 2FA sometimes with different names. You need to enable it. Second factors can usually be received by SMS or in an authentication app (unique one-time access code).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Authentication can be in the form of: a PIN you know, a phone you have, a biometric such as a fingerprint.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Google Authenticator is one of the popular and easy to use apps for 2FA.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnet.com/how-to/how-and-why-to-use-two-factor-authentication/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/EXbjJUD2sH0&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
        <question id="acces-q50" type="A" hidden="false">
            <text>In the software systems you develop, do you force the users to use personal accounts?</text>
            <attachments/>
            <options correct="acces-q50o1">
                <option id="acces-q50o1">
                    <text>YES, OUR SYSTEMS FORCE ALL USERS TO USE PERSONAL ACCOUNTS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q50o2">
                    <text>NO, SOME SYSTEMS DO NOT REQUIRE PERSONAL ACCOUNTS FOR SOME FEATURES</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q50o3">
                    <text>NO, MOST SYSTEMS DO NOT REQUIRE PERSONAL ACCOUNTS FOR SOME FEATURES</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
