            <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Address poor cyber hygiene! &lt;/strong&gt;Each user should have a unique account in a system. It is important to prevent those users who do not have permission to access some resources.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/en/SSB27U_6.4.0/com.ibm.zvm.v640.hcpa6/hcpa6361.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why having personal accounts is essential!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Creating an audit trail is difficult for shared accounts and accountability becomes a problem.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Shared accounts have problems in applying password policies. They have poor static passwords and vulnerable regarding password guessing attacks.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Shared accounts make a possibility of unauthorised access, for instance by former employees&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sans.org/reading-room/whitepapers/basics/administration-shared-accounts-1271&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Educate and enforce users to prevent using shared/group accounts!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Common bad habits among SMEs&amp;rsquo; employees: &lt;/strong&gt;sharing work email passwords with colleagues or assistants&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/1747499/Content%20Downloads/Switchfast_SMB_Cybersecurity_Report.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                    <attachment id="acces-q50p1" mime="image/jpeg"><content filename="acces-q50p1.jpg" xml:lang="de"></content>
                    </attachment>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
        <question id="acces-q60" type="A" hidden="false">
            <text>Do you force users to use strong passwords?</text>
            <attachments/>
            <options correct="acces-q60o1">
                <option id="acces-q60o1">
                    <text>YES, WE FORCE ALL USERS TO USE STRONG PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q60o2">
                    <text>MOST USERS USE STRONG PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q60o3">
                    <text>SOME USERS MAY USE STRONG PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
                <option id="acces-q60o4">
                    <text>NO, WE DID NOT ASK USERS TO USE STRONG PASSWORDS</text>
                    <attachments></attachments>
                </option>
            </options>
            <listeners/>
            <metadata key="scores">
                <mvalue key="acces-q60o1">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
                <mvalue key="acces-q60o2">
                    <stringValue>50</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <metadata key="nextQid">
                <mvalue key="default">
                    <stringValue>acces-q70</stringValue>
                </mvalue>
            </metadata>
            <instruction>
                <text>
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Avoid predictable passwords! &lt;/strong&gt;Strong password (considering minimum requirements) is fundamental to protect against &lt;strong&gt;Dictionary Attacks or Password Guessing. &lt;/strong&gt;Many people tend to select a single word or short password and it is predictable in a short period.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://authanvil.com/blog/3-types-of-password-security-attacks-and-how-to-avoid-them&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turn on Password Protection! &lt;/strong&gt;63% of small business cyber breaches occurred because of weak or stolen passwords.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.asbfeo.gov.au/sites/default/files/documents/ASBFEO-cyber-security-research-report.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet certain criteria when you manage a password!&lt;/strong&gt; Password strength is not the same as the password length. A password should be meaningful (so memorable) to you but difficult (cryptic) to guess for the others (or specialized software).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Strong passwords: Have at least 8 characters, Contain both upper and lower case, Have at least one numerical character, Have at least one special character&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Do not write down passwords on sticky notes&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create a cryptic password.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to solve the memory problem?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply Passphrase instead of Password: &lt;/strong&gt;First, make an easy to remember phrase, then select the first character of each word, then use upper/lower case and finally, you can exchange special characters by numbers.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply Password Managers: &lt;/strong&gt;You can have a master password to save long, complex passwords&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/en/SSKTMJ_8.5.3/com.ibm.help.domino.admin85.doc/H_PASSWORD_QUALITY_SCALE_UNDERSTANDING_AND_SETTING_DEFAULTS_STEPS.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More info ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://password.kaspersky.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Check if your Password is strong enough!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.checktool.ch/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Check if your account was compromised (Swiss)!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/VYzguTdOmmU&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
                </text>
                <attachments>
                </attachments>
            </instruction>
        </question>
